  "description": "One of the two foundational Arabica lineages. Seeds were taken from the natural coffee forests of Southwestern Ethiopia to Yemen, where it was cultivated as a crop. From Yemen, Typica dispersed globally — arriving in Brazil in the early 1700s and dominating Central American plantations until the 1940s. Because it is low-yielding and highly susceptible to disease, it was gradually replaced by Bourbon derivatives. 100% Typica is becoming increasingly rare in high-end specialty coffee, making verified lots a significant find.",
